title: Israeli PM refuses to comment on alleged gifts from billionaire James Packer - 9news.com.au
text:
Israeli PM refuses to comment on alleged gifts from billionaire James Packer By 9NEWS 
Israel’s Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu has refused to comment on allegations he received gifts from Australian billionaire businessman James Packer. 
Israeli police are investigating allegations Mr Netanyahu accepted expensive gifts from a movie mogul and Mr Packer, who reportedly provided luxury holidays for Mr Netanyahu's son as he is good friends with the prime minister. 
During a press conference at Kirribilli House today, 9NEWS reporter Mark Burrows asked Mr Netanyahu about the allegations. 
“Obviously I’m not going to comment on details, but I think nothing will come of it,” he said. 
“There is nothing there except friendship.” 
Prime Minister Malcolm Turnbull, standing beside Mr Netanyahu, said he had “nothing further” to add. 
“It’s an investigation. It will run its course,” he said. 
Watch the full story on 9NEWS Sydney at 6pm © Nine Digital Pty Ltd 2017
